parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manual transmission shift lever can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift lever breaks off or falls out of the console
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the transmission is stuck in a particular gear
the driver is unable to operate the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the transmission is stuck in a particular gear
the driver is unable to operate the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine/transmission mount can cause the engine to shift, leading to damage to other engine mounts, axles, and potentially causing the engine to fall to the ground, resulting in loss of control and accidents.
The failure of the turbo can cause the engine to fail, resulting in a loss of power and potentially leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Explosion or loud noise from the turbo

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the rod to toss through the engine block, resulting in catastrophic engine failure, loss of control, and potentially leading to accidents or fires.
symptoms: and smoke or oil coming out of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient oil level or low oil pressure can cause engine failure, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or fires.
symptoms: No indication of low oil level or pressure until after engine failure
dash low oil pressure indicator light comes on after engine stops running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter rod can cause the shifter to break off, leaving the driver unable to shift gears, which can lead to accidents, stalling, or stranding.
symptoms: The shifter breaks off in the driver's hand
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
